<p>The <b>Spiritual Exercises of <a href="/wiki/Ignatius_of_Loyola" title="Ignatius of Loyola">Ignatius of Loyola</a></b>, (written within 1522-1524) are a brief set of <a href="/wiki/Meditation" title="Meditation">meditations</a>, <a href="/wiki/Prayer" title="Prayer">prayers</a> and mental exercises, available in various book formats, designed to be carried out over a period of 28 to 30 days. The book is approximately 200 pages long. They were written with the intention of enhancing and strengthening one's faith-experience in a manner that has distinctly <a href="/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Church" title="Roman Catholic Church">Roman Catholic</a> aspects.</p>
